I just watched #BrittanyRunsAMarathon and i cried the whole time.

Not only because I worked on it as a background actor as an “elite runner” (and did I have some notes for production that day!) but because running the #NYCmarathon is so incredibly special and what she goes through is so common and we who love running and love the sport absolutely can be overwhelming but once you get over hating us for being a skinny bitch whom is perceived to have a perfect life you find out that no one’s life is as perfect as it seems and taking responsibility is a beautiful thing and quite frankly all we ever want to do in the name of the love of the sport is to help you be better #StrongLooksDifferentOnEveryone
